cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification using deep neural network models and focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning models, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of standard protocols for training, which is related to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of multimedia and has applications in surveillance and forensics, which could fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of person re-identification for robotics, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Robotics).
